Package: fiRetools
Title: Vegetation Fire Threshold Classification
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Grant", "Williamson", , "grant.williamson@utas.edu.au", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-3469-7550"))
Description: FireTools is a spatial processing system to produce maps, timeseries and landscape metric analysis of optimum vegetation fire intervals.  Input data comprises vector GIS files of vegetation class, fire history, and a look-up table with vegetation fire attributes (eg. maximum and minimum burn interval) and classifies vegetation into within threshold, vulnerable, over burnt, or long unburnt categories.
